physdesc.extent: 26 manuscript boxes, 2 oversize boxes, 1 album box, 1 envelope

did.abstract: Correspondence, speeches and writings, memoranda, reports, studies, bulletins, statistical data, and maps, relating to economic conditions and food supply in Europe during World War I, postwar reconstruction, and activities of the War Trade Board, Food Administration, and American Relief Administration

scopecontent.p: Correspondence, business cards, diary, identity passes, passports, schedule and miscellany relating to the life and work of Alonzo Taylor, arranged alphabetically by physical form
Articles, remarks and speeches arranged chronologically by title

Agreements, articles, bulletins, charts and maps, clippings, correspondence, financial records, inventory, interview, issue of licenses for export and import of food to different parts of Europe, memoranda, minutes of meetings, notes, printed matter, remarks, reports, statements and telegrams relating to the allocation, exports and imports, requirements, production and deliveries of food to different countries of Europe during World War I, arranged by physical form. Includes the records of various departments of the United States Government, such as Council of National Defense, Export Administrative Board, State Department, War Industries Board, involved in the war time efforts to deal with distribution of food and related problems and postwar reconstruction in Europe

Agreements, correspondence, memoranda, minutes of meetings, notes, organizational records, press release, printed matter, reports, statistical data sheets, survey, and telegrams relating to the activities of the War Trade Board, arranged by physical form

Applications, clippings, correspondence, financial records, memoranda, notes, reports and statistical records relating to the American relief efforts in Europe, arranged by physical form. Includes information relating to the economic situation in Germany, the effects of embargo and the conditions in German prison camps

Articles, clippings, correspondence, charts, conference proceedings, data sheets, maps, memoranda, minutes of meetings, notes and telegrams relating to the domestic production, exports and imports of food in Denmark, the Netherlands, Norway and Switzerland, arranged alphabetically by the name of the country

1 album consisting of 12 prints depicting American relief activities in Poland following World War I, American Feast in Warsaw, Polish children's kitchens and schools, 1921; and 1 print depicting Alonzo Taylor, n.d.
